      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LENNYSTAR (2) has been thereabouts against tougher opposition in her two runs back down in Vic. Makes her stable debut for the Chau camp and looks well placed to play a major role. AUSTRALASIA (3) ran below her best at Doomben last time when giving away a big start but her prior form measures up nicely for this sort of contest. Gets in well with the 2kg claim and can bounce back sharply. Big threat. SIGLO DE ORO (1) resumes after six months and looks ready following a Gold Coast trial win. Should settle handy in the run from the inside pillar and holds winning claims. OUR SPARKY (5) was knocking on the door through last campaign without striking. Has been readied with a handy trial win and has to be included.",
